-- CANADA RESEARCH ROUNDUP-Gildan Activewear, Transalta Renewables, Vermilion Energy 
-- 
-- Mon May 05, 2014 02:49AM EDT
-- None



May 5 (Reuters) - Securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several Canadian companies, including Transalta Renewables and Vermilion Energy, on Monday.

HIGHLIGHTS   * Canadian REIT <REF_u.TO>: Canaccord Genuity raises price target to C$46.50; rating buy   * Transalta Renewables <RNW.TO>: NBF resumes coverage with sector perform rating * Vermilion Energy <VET.TO>: National Bank Financial raises price target to C$80 from C$72   Following is a summary of research actions on Canadian companies reported by Reuters on Monday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order.  * Brookfield Renewable Energy <BEP_u.TO>: NBF ups target to C$33.50 from C$32;sector perform * Canadian REIT <REF_u.TO>: Canaccord Genuity raises price target to C$46.50; rating buy * Copper Mountain Mining <CUM.TO>: Canaccord Genuity raises target to C$2.80 from C$2.70 * Gildan Activewear <GIL.TO>: National Bank Financial raises target to C$69 from C$67 * Gildan Activewear <GIL.N>: DA Davidson raises target price to $64 from $60; rating buy * Torstar Corp <TSb.TO>: RBC raises price target to C$9 from C$7; rating sector perform * Transalta Renewables <RNW.TO>: NBF resumes coverage with sector perform rating * Vermilion Energy <VET.TO>: National Bank Financial raises price target to C$80 from C$72 * Western Energy <WRG.TO>: RBC raises target price to C$13 from C$11; rating outperform